import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='CO2', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['CO2'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean CO2')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['CO2'] = pd.to_numeric(data['CO2'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='CO2', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean: {data["CO2"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 levels?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Date'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='CO2', data=data, ax=ax, label='CO2')
    sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='adjusted_CO2', data=data, ax=ax, label='Adjusted CO2')
    plt.axhline(y=data['CO2_diff'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean CO2 Difference')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Month'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Month'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce').dt.month_name()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Month', y='CO2', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['CO2'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean CO2: {data["CO2"].mean():.2f}')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Date')
    data['CO2_diff'] = data['CO2_diff'].astype(float)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='CO2_diff', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['CO2_diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean CO2 Difference')
    plt.title('What is the difference in CO2 levels between consecutive months?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
